The African National Congress is facing competition in two of its strongholds in KZN. This is in the latest round of local by-elections held Wednesday in KZN, Western Cape and the Eastern Cape. By-elections analyst Wayne Sussman spoke to #eNCA. #DStv403  DURBAN - The Inkatha Freedom Party was the biggest winner in this week’s by-elections in rural areas of KZN according to elections analyst, Wayne Sussman. READ: SA's electricity crisis | IFP says government has failed the nation Sussman says the IFP took votes from the ANC in Msunduzi, an area historically dominated by the ruling party. Watch the video above for more details on this story.